{"tid":2233272,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"英國外長藍韜文不排除杯葛2022北京冬奧可能性","createTime":"2020-10-07T04:13:35.000Z","updateTime":"2020-10-07T10:06:52.000Z","uid":78892,"like":93,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":26,"replies":[{"pid":"c00b7bdc6077f9d83450ad46cd47a67c5652f166","tid":2233272,"uid":78892,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T04:13:35.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/HtgXSxA.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FHtgXSxA.png&h=42566400&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n汁：<a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-54441143\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-politics-54441143&d=lMjb5htdGhqouCxjtFETmS3KoYHjImyLH66vjnFGY4M%3D&h=073b7839\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-politics-54441143&h=4162dd27\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-54441143</a><br />\n係咪日出了<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n因侵犯人框而被英國威脅杯葛嘅北京2022冬奧，簡稱欣澳<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"bbe4d186abacc9f419092016d4587db4c9d3da34","tid":2233272,"uid":78892,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T04:14:02.000Z","msg":"侵犯人權<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"27268eb091257aa2e5b05347b05ef9005c1bde33","tid":2233272,"uid":78892,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T04:15:54.000Z","msg":"Mr Raab was appearing at the Foreign Affairs Select Committee and was asked about what the UK was doing to combat persecution of Uighur Muslims.<br />\n<br />\nHe said: &quot;In the UK, our concerns can only be growing about the reports of what's happening in Xinjinag and we would want to work very closely with our international partners to give the most powerful message, whether it is in the UN... or whether it is in applying sanctions.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;We do need to look at what action to take. The concerns of what's happening to the Uighurs, the detention, the mistreatment, the forced sterilisation, is something that we cannot just turn away from.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nThe foreign secretary said the UK needed to &quot;call them out [and] hold China to account&quot;, adding: &quot;We need to be making the point to China, as a country that rightly has expectations to be treated as a leading member of the international community, that this is at odds with the responsibilities that come with being a leading member of the international community.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n'Further action'<br />\n<br />\nAsked by fellow Conservative MP Alicia Kearns whether boycotting the Winter Games in 2022 would send a strong message, Mr Raab said: &quot;Generally speaking my instinct is to separate sport from diplomacy and politics but there comes a point where that may not be possible.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;I would say, let's gather the evidence, let's work with international partners, let's consider it further in the round with further action we need to take.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nThe chair of the committee, Conservative Tom Tugenhadt, also asked Mr Raab whether he would encourage the Duke of Cambridge whether to attend on behalf of the British government.<br />\n<br />\nThe foreign secretary said that decision would be &quot;part of a wider process&quot; and he would look at it &quot;very closely and carefully&quot;."},{"pid":"886080d1ecec2abc53a1f228db1e372060ae6806","tid":2233272,"uid":15815,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T04:18:53.000Z","msg":"仲未肯釋懷?<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/yo.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0af0c24ec316eb94c4ed6b87b92d3f411240223f","tid":2233272,"uid":2110,"like":8,"dislike":1,"score":7,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T04:19:03.000Z","msg":"政府杯無用...<br />\n班運動員照奶, 當然佢地唔係奶個政權, 只要純粹想參加<br 